Get More Done With a Perspective Power Hour
-------------------------------------------

By Trudi Roth

A CEO client recently confessed to me, =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m so busy on
back-to-back video calls that I don=E2=80=99t even have time for a
bathroom break.=E2=80=9D

That was no humblebrag. It was a clear, relatable illustration of
the dangers of over-accessibility, which research shows lead to
stress and burnout (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/xmu7mwpvl4h6h07m3ef5/n2hohqungpv4keu0/aH=
R0cHM6Ly9mdXJ0aGVyLm5ldC9iZWF0LWJ1cm5vdXQv
).

While multitasking is a hallmark of our digital age, it=E2=80=99s nothing
new. Anyone with a busy job and personal life can lose sight of
the forest through the trees.

Luckily, there=E2=80=99s a simple technique you can use to overcome
overwhelm pioneered by the legendary diplomat, author, teacher,
and businessman George P. Schultz, who recently passed away at
100.

In the =E2=80=9980s, when he served as Reagan=E2=80=99s secretary of state,
Schultz would shut the door of his office, grab a pen and paper,
and declare himself unavailable for one hour. (Only the president
or his wife could interrupt.) In that small window, he made ample
room to think big.

Daydream Believer
-----------------

Schultz led a jam-packed life, notably holding four cabinet-level
positions under two presidents. Commanding respect from both
sides of the aisle, he tackled some of the greatest threats of
our times, from nuclear proliferation to climate change.

In 2017, New York Times journalist David Leonhardt shared
Schultz=E2=80=99s secret sauce. As he recounts:

Schultz told me that his hour of solitude was the only way he
could find time to think about the strategic aspects of his job.
Otherwise, he would be constantly pulled into moment-to-moment
tactical issues, never able to focus on larger questions of the
national interest. And the only way to do great work, in any
field, is to find time to consider the larger questions.
In other words, Schultz made space for purposeful daydreaming.

When your mind wanders, your mental default mode network (
https://click.convertkit-mail2.com/xmu7mwpvl4h6h07m3ef5/48hvh7u09em3nwaq/aH=
R0cHM6Ly93d3cucHN5Y2hvbG9neXRvZGF5LmNvbS91cy9iYXNpY3MvZGVmYXVsdC1tb2RlLW5ld=
Hdvcms=3D
